The paper deals with the algorithmic information and randomness of sequences, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), cryptography (cs.CR), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mutual dimension and coupled randomness also suggests a focus on mathematical analysis and probability theory, which are relevant to all of these sub-categories.
